# Advisories suppressed in `scripts/cve_audit.py` with rationale.
# Format: <advisory_id>: <one-line rationale>
# Reviewers MUST re-check this file when bumping the underlying
# crate version — a CVE that didn't apply at version N might
# apply at version N+1.

RUSTSEC-2023-0071: Marvin attack on rsa crate. Affects RSA PRIVATE-key decrypt timing side channel. Sphragis only uses the rsa crate for X.509 certificate signature VERIFICATION (public-key op) in src/net/x509.rs — no private-key decrypt anywhere in tree. Reconfirm at every Cargo.lock bump of the rsa crate.
